solutions.content:
If the operands were only single digits then it would be so much easier!
*But they aren't*
Okay, then what if we already knew what the operands would be? Then we would only have to check for the 3 possible operators between every 2 operands which would be 3^(number of operands-1)
*How to get these pre-decided operands then..*
Bit-Manipulation to the rescue:-
	We only have to divide num into all possible operands and for each of these divisions check all the possible expressions it makes.
```
Finding all possible operand divisions from num and store them in a list -> 2^(length of num-1){
	checking all the expressions these operands make -> 3^(size of the list of operands-1)
}
I dont know how to find the exact complexity but it would be something like ->
2^(length(num)-1) * 3^(m) where m ranges from [0,length(num)-1]
```

Java Implementation : 
```
class Solution {
    public List<String> addOperators(String num, int target) {
        int n = num.length()-1;
        t = target;
        list = new ArrayList<>();
        outer : for(int i=0;i<(1<<n);i++){
            List<Long> arr = new ArrayList<>();
            long cur = num.charAt(0)-'0';
            for(int j=0;j<n;j++){
                if((i&(1<<j))!=0){
                    arr.add(cur);
                    cur = num.charAt(j+1)-'0';
                }   
                else{
                    if(cur==0) continue outer;
                    cur = cur*10 + (num.charAt(j+1)-'0');
                }
            }
            arr.add(cur);
            rec(arr.get(0),1,arr.get(0),arr.size(),""+arr.get(0),0,arr);
        }
        return list;
    }

    public void rec(long eval, int i, long prev, int n, String exp, int type, List<Long> num){
        if(i==n){
            if(eval==t) list.add(exp);
            return;
        }
        long cur = num.get(i);
        rec(eval+cur,i+1,cur,n,exp+("+"+cur),0,num);
        rec(eval-cur,i+1,cur,n,exp+("-"+cur),1,num);
        if(type==0) rec(eval-prev+prev*cur,i+1,prev*cur,n,exp+("*"+cur),0,num);
        else rec(eval+prev-prev*cur,i+1,prev*cur,n,exp+("*"+cur),1,num); 
    }

    public List<String> list;
    public int t;
}
