solutions.content:
To remove random restriction on length with two-node approach.
Each time we split the list between ``start`` and ``end``  into two halves and do a rand()%2 to pick which half.
If the list contains odd number of nodes, we do extra rand()%2 to decide if ``middle`` node goes to 1st or 2nd half.

Case0: ``node1->null``
Simply return value of node1
Case1:``node1->node2->null``
Split into two halves (``node1->node2`` or ``node2->null``) and rand()%2 to decide where to go.
Set new ``start`` and ``end`` node accordingly and loop it. Note: ``end`` is excluded.
Case2: ``node1->node2->node3->null``
Split into two halves. Extra rand()%2 to decide if ``node2`` belongs to 1st or 2nd half.
``node1->node2`` or ``node1->node2->node3`` or ``node2->node3->null`` or ``node3->null``

Probability Explaination:
For even case, it's clear that half of the nodes between ``start`` and ``end`` will be selected.
For odd case, the ``middle`` node's chance being selected
P(Belong1st & Select1st) + P(Belong2nd & Select2nd) = 2/4 = 50%

Performance Explaination:
S(n) = O(1)
T(n) = n+n/2+n/4+n/8+... < 2n = O(n)

```
class Solution {
private:
    ListNode* head;
public:
    /** @param head The linked list's head.
        Note that the head is guaranteed to be not null, so it contains at least one node. */
    Solution(ListNode* head) {
        this->head = head;
    }

    /** Returns a random node's value. */
    int getRandom() {
        ListNode *start = head, *end = nullptr, *fast = nullptr, *slow = nullptr;
        while(start->next != end) {
            bool even = true;
            fast = start;
            slow = start;
            while(fast != end) {
                fast = fast->next;
                if (fast == end) {
                    even = false;
                } else {
                    fast = fast->next;
                }
                if (even) { // For odd case, we do extra rand()%2 later, hence save a previous
                    slow = slow->next;
                }
            }
            if (!even && (rand()%2)) {
                slow = slow->next;
            }
            if (rand()%2) {
                start = slow;
            } else {
                end = slow;
            }
        }
        return start->val;
    }
};
```

