**Solution #1:**

Naive alorithm which constructs the answer in reverse order.  Reverse order because the first group of the answer is the only group allowed to have less than `K` characters, thus we need to greedily take `K` characters for all but the first group).

---

*Kotlin*
```
class Solution {
    fun licenseKeyFormatting(S: String, K: Int): String {
        var ans = mutableListOf<Char>()
        S.toUpperCase().reversed().filter {
            it != '-'
        }.forEachIndexed { i, c ->
            if (0 < i && i % K == 0)
                ans.add('-')
            ans.add(c)
        }
        return ans.reversed().joinToString("")
    }
}
```

