# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Since we need to group 'k' chars together, we can start from the end and separate the groups with '-' and it automatically group k or < k items as first group.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We'll construct the required output in reverse fashion.
Read the string from the end and form the reverse of the desired string. In the end, reverse the string.

### Please upvote if you liked the solution :)

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n) as we need to loop over the string once

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n) as we use string builder for building the new string.

# Code
```
public class Solution {
    public string LicenseKeyFormatting(string s, int k) {
        int cnt = k;
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();

        for (int i = s.Length - 1; i >= 0; i--)
        {
            if (s[i] == '-')
                continue;

            sb.Append(s[i]);
            cnt--;

            if (cnt == 0)
            {
                sb.Append('-');
                cnt = k;
            }
        }

        sb = new StringBuilder(sb.ToString().Trim('-'));
        int x = 0;
        int y = sb.Length - 1;
        while (x < y)
        {
            char c = sb[x];
            sb[x] = sb[y];
            sb[y] = c;
            x++;
            y--;
        }

        return sb.ToString().ToUpper();
    }
}
```

