solutions.content:
**Idea:**
* Skip leading and trailing dashes. Ignore dashes in the loop as well, they're irrelevant.
* After skipping you'd have start and end pointers to the relevant alpha-numeric sub-string. Process this substring
* Since grouping is to be done such that later groups are filled first, so start forming groups from the end of the substring
* Build k-size group and append dash when size reached.
* Don't append dash if beginning of substring is reached since we don't want a leading dash
* Restore size when a group is formed
* Reverse reformatted string at the end to get the result
>**T/S:** O(n)/O(n), where n = size(s)
```
public String licenseKeyFormatting(String s, int k) {
	var i = 0;
	var j = s.length() - 1;
	var groupSize = k;

	while (i < s.length() && s.charAt(i) == '-')
		i++;
	while (j >= 0 && s.charAt(j) == '-')
		j--;

	var reformatted = new StringBuilder();
	while (j >= i) {
		if (s.charAt(j) != '-') {
			reformatted.append(Character.toUpperCase(s.charAt(j)));

			if (--groupSize == 0 && j != i) {
				reformatted.append('-');
				groupSize = k;
			}
		}
		j--;
	}

	return reformatted.reverse()
					  .toString();
}
```
